{%- if identity_provider == "None - Manual User Management" %}

### Manual User Management Selected

You have chosen to manage users manually without SCIM integration. This means:
- Users must be created directly in Snowflake
- User deprovisioning must be done manually when employees leave
- No automatic synchronization with an Identity Provider

**What's next:**
- The Create Account Administrators step will guide you through creating admin users manually
- Consider implementing SCIM in the future to improve security and reduce administrative overhead

{%- else %}

### SCIM Integration Selected: {{ identity_provider }}

You have chosen automated user provisioning via SCIM. This means:
- Users will be automatically created when added to your IdP
- Users will be automatically disabled when removed from your IdP
- Centralized identity management from your IdP

**What's next:**
- The Configure SCIM Integration step will guide you through setting up the SCIM connection
- The Provision Account Administrators step will help you assign admin roles to SCIM-provisioned users

{%- endif %}

{%- if configure_saml == "Yes - Configure SAML now" %}

### SAML/SSO Configuration

You will configure SAML/SSO in a dedicated step. This enables:
- Users can log in using their IdP credentials (single sign-on)
- Centralized authentication control from your IdP
- Seamless user experience without separate Snowflake passwords

{%- else %}

### SAML/SSO Deferred

You have chosen to skip SAML configuration for now. Users will authenticate with:
- Snowflake username and password
- Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) for security

You can configure SAML later without rebuilding your environment.

{%- endif %}